snippet.title: THE BENGAL FILES Official Trailer | Vivek Agnihotri | Abhishek A | Pallavi J | Zee Studios | 5 Sept
snippet.description:
From the makers of The Kashmir Files and The Tashkent Files, here is the official trailer of THE BENGAL FILES, the powerful conclusion to the trilogy by two-time National Award-winning filmmaker Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri.

A presentation by: Tej Narayan & Snehlatha Agarwal and I Am Buddha

Directed by: Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri
Produced by: Abhishek Agarwal, Pallavi Joshi and Vivek Ranjan Agnihotri 
Worldwide Release: Zee Studios
Music: Zee Music Co.
Starring: Mithun Chakraborty, Anupam Kher, Pallavi Joshi, Darshan Kumaar, Simratt Kaur

This September, witness the untold truth of the Hindu genocide.

snippet.title: Rippan Swaamy Official Trailer | Vijay Raghavendra | Ashwini Chandrashekar | Kishor Mudubidire | PRK
snippet.description:
Panchaanana Films productions in association with PRK Audio
presents
Rippan Swaamy - A rural thriller set in the fictional Malnad village of Snana Kopa.
The story unfolds after the mysterious suicide of Rippan Swaamy, leading to a trail of secrets, drama, and suspense. As the mystery deepens, the truth behind his name and death slowly unravels.

The film is set to release in theatres on August 29.
 üéµ Listen to the soulful songs exclusively on PRK Audio.

Production House: Panchaanana Films
Directed by: Kishor Mudubidire
Produced by: Panchaanana Films

Hiqaan Utte Takk Lagge Yaariyan De Tamgge,
Saare Hall Hege Banda Jehra Jiwe Samjhe,
Ooo Billo Saanu Vairy Vi Chahida Koi Chajjda,
Ni Howe Jehra Sahmne Hiqqan De Wich Vajjda,
Takkraange Akhri Saahan Te Kujh Bann Ke,
Shdd Ke Maidaan Nai Khadak Siyon Bhajjda,
Bas Neeli Shatt Wale Agge Hath Jorihye, Ni Ayinn Langh Janda Mitran Da.....
Langh Janda Mitran Da Din Goriye, Ni Ayinn Langh Janda Mitran Da Din Goriye,
Kiton Mudhde Nai Mela Lutte Bin Goriye, Ni Ayinn Langh Janda Mitran Da Din Goriye.....

The Sinquefield Cup 2025 is the final event of the Grand Chess Tour. It is a classical event and held in Saint Louis, USA.

Players:
Caruana (2784)
Praggnanandhaa (2779)
Gukesh (2776)
Abdusattorov (2771)
Firouzja (2766)
Wesley So (2745)
Levon Aronian (2737)
Maxime Vachier Lagrave (2736)
Jan Krzysztof Duda (2725)
Sam Sevian (2683)

Pairings of round 2
Pragg vs Caruana
Aronian vs Sevian
Wesley vs MVL
Alirejza vs Duda
Gukesh vs Abdusattorov

Schedule : 
The Sinquefield Cup 2025 starts on 18th of August 2025 and ends the 28th of August 2025. 23rd of August is a rest day. Each day the games begin at 1 a.m. IST (So the event actually begins on 19th in India).

Format : 
The time control is 90 minutes for the first 40 moves, followed by 30 more minutes for the rest of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one.

Prize money: 
The total prize fund is US$350,000 and the first prize is US$100,000. 
1st place - US$100,000
2nd place - US$65,000
3rd place - US$48,000
4th place - US$32,000
5th place -  US$26,000
6th place - US$21,000
7th place - US$18,500
8th place -  US$16,000
9th place - US$13,000
10th place - US$10,500

MVL: 28
Aronian: 23.5
Firouzja: 22.5
Caruana: 20.5
Praggnanandhaa: 20
Wesley So: 19.5
Abdusattorov: 18
Gukesh: 16
Duda: 11

Points at stake in this event: 
1st place -12 or 13* 
2nd place - 10
3rd place - 8
4th place - 7
5th place - 6
6th place - 5
7th place - 4
8th place - 3
9th place - 2
10th place - 1

Top 4 players in the Grand chess tour standings will make it to the Grand Chess Tour final which will be held in Brazil from 26th of September to 4th October 2025. The Sinquefield Cup is the final event in the Grand Chess Tour.
